WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.960
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.052 --> 00:00:07.260
BERNIE TELSEY: Hi, everybody.

00:00:07.260 --> 00:00:08.360
My name is Bernie Telsey.

00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:11.750
I'm one of the artistic
directors of MCC Theater.

00:00:11.750 --> 00:00:13.820
For those of you
who don't know, MCC

00:00:13.820 --> 00:00:17.420
is a not-for-profit theater
that's been around 33 years.

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:20.990
We just moved into our own new
complex, the Robert W Wilson

00:00:20.990 --> 00:00:24.680
MCC Theater Space
on 52nd Street.

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:25.880
So you all must come by.

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:27.630
We have two new theaters.

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:30.007
And the opening of our
building is our new production,

00:00:30.007 --> 00:00:32.090
which we're here today to
talk a little bit about,

00:00:32.090 --> 00:00:33.590
which is called
"Alice by Heart,"

00:00:33.590 --> 00:00:36.260
by this incredible
creative team.

00:00:36.260 --> 00:00:36.920
So welcome.

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:38.810
I'm going to
introduce everybody.

00:00:38.810 --> 00:00:42.230
"Alice" is written by Steven
Sater and Jessie Nelson.

00:00:42.230 --> 00:00:44.030
And the music is
by Duncan Sheik.

00:00:44.030 --> 00:00:47.970
Also lyrics by Steven Sater,
and our director, Jessie Nelson.

00:00:47.970 --> 00:00:51.590
So this is our creative team,
along with our two stars.

00:00:51.590 --> 00:00:53.840
Molly Gordon is playing Alice.

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:56.750
And Colton Ryan is
playing the White Rabbit.

00:00:56.750 --> 00:00:59.900
And we also have Jason
Hart, our musical director.

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:01.221
How is everybody today?

00:01:01.221 --> 00:01:01.846
AUDIENCE: Whoo.

00:01:01.846 --> 00:01:02.310
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:02.310 --> 00:01:04.643
BERNIE TELSEY: All right, you
going to come see "Alice"?

00:01:04.643 --> 00:01:06.560
Yes, all right, very good.

00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:09.940
So to start off, we're to do
a little bit of a few songs

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:11.690
so you can get a sense
of what "Alice" is.

00:01:11.690 --> 00:01:14.603
And then we'll do a little Q
and A with our creative team.

00:01:14.603 --> 00:01:16.020
But if we could
start, I was going

00:01:16.020 --> 00:01:18.620
to have Steven just tell us
a little bit about "Alice

00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:21.740
by Heart" so you know
what is this story

00:01:21.740 --> 00:01:25.210
and he can set up our
first song, called "Still."

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:28.030
STEVEN SATER: OK, is
this working good?

00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:29.853
BERNIE TELSEY: Yeah.

00:01:29.853 --> 00:01:31.520
STEVEN SATER: "Alice
by Heart" is really

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:34.130
about the power of the
imagination to get us

00:01:34.130 --> 00:01:35.240
through the hardest times.

00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:38.270
What a book can mean to
you as a young person

00:01:38.270 --> 00:01:40.820
and how you can carry it
through life with you.

00:01:40.820 --> 00:01:43.400
So it feels kind of
increasingly urgent to us

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:47.840
in what feels like a
culturally challenged time.

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:51.890
And so, it's set during the
bombing of London, known

00:01:51.890 --> 00:01:54.555
as the Blitz, in 1940 and 1941.

00:01:54.555 --> 00:01:55.910
It went on for months.

00:01:55.910 --> 00:01:58.250
There were 59 straight
nights of bombs

00:01:58.250 --> 00:01:59.900
being dropped on the city.

00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:02.270
And the citizens, to
protect themselves,

00:02:02.270 --> 00:02:04.370
began huddling in
shelters at night.

00:02:04.370 --> 00:02:05.750
They were night bombings.

00:02:05.750 --> 00:02:07.890
Or increasingly
in tube stations,

00:02:07.890 --> 00:02:09.680
in the subway stations.

00:02:09.680 --> 00:02:13.130
And there's a young
girl, Alice, who's

00:02:13.130 --> 00:02:15.770
been bombed out of her home.

00:02:15.770 --> 00:02:18.410
And she finds
shelter for herself

00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:23.570
in this kind of makeshift
encampment in a tube station.

00:02:23.570 --> 00:02:27.470
And what she loves most in the
world is this boy named Alfred.

00:02:27.470 --> 00:02:29.480
And he's found.

00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:31.130
And he's brought down.

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:34.850
And they reunite in
the tube station.

00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:36.780
And it's so dire there.

00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:40.980
And they're under the care of
an unfeeling Red Cross nurse.

00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:43.970
And she says-- he's
ailing so much.

00:02:43.970 --> 00:02:46.040
He's contracted illness,
living on the streets,

00:02:46.040 --> 00:02:47.240
drinking out of gutters.

00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:49.612
She says, all this, we
can make it disappear.

00:02:49.612 --> 00:02:51.320
You can run there,
you can breathe there.

00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:52.310
Let's go back to Wonderland.

00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:54.020
He says, I have no
time for all that.

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:55.880
And she starts reading the book.

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:57.090
The book is taken from her.

00:02:57.090 --> 00:02:58.580
She says I know it all by heart.

00:02:58.580 --> 00:03:00.780
She starts reciting the book.

00:03:00.780 --> 00:03:04.940
And lo and behold, this anthemic
Duncan Sheik theme kicks in.

00:03:04.940 --> 00:03:07.370
And they're transported
to Wonderland.

00:03:07.370 --> 00:03:11.150
And this song, "Still,"
is their first moment

00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:12.920
together in Wonderland.

00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:16.550
And it shows their
central conflict.

00:03:16.550 --> 00:03:18.182
He feels-- he's
the White Rabbit.

00:03:18.182 --> 00:03:20.390
He's late, he's late, he
has no time, he has no time.

00:03:20.390 --> 00:03:22.932
She's not getting it, that what
he's saying on a deeper level

00:03:22.932 --> 00:03:24.470
is he's going to die.

00:03:24.470 --> 00:03:27.230
She says, no, we're
in Wonderland again.

00:03:27.230 --> 00:03:30.590
We can be in our golden
afternoon, in our garden.

00:03:30.590 --> 00:03:34.210
Stay with me, linger with
me, play with me still.

00:03:34.210 --> 00:03:35.393
So that's the song.

00:03:35.393 --> 00:03:37.560
DUNCAN SHEIK: So Colton and
Molly, will you join us?

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:38.060
Great.

00:03:43.696 --> 00:03:50.040
[COLTON RYAN AND MOLLY GORDON
 SINGING "STILL"]

